### Describe the bug


I'm having an issue with logging out. My server is acting as a Backend-For-Front-End Gateway. It handles the cookie and token management for logging in using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.OpenIdConnect. And it proxies API requests using YARP. There is no javascript library and no tokens in the browser. Only the cookie from the server.

The initial login to Azure B2C works fine. And once the user has logged in, the user can click a Logout button in the UI which navigates to an /auth/logout endpoint in the server that does the following:

```
app.MapGet("/auth/logout", (string? redirectUrl, HttpContext ctx) =>
        {
            if (string.IsNullOrEmpty(redirectUrl))
            {
                redirectUrl = "/";
            }

            ctx.Session.Clear();

            var authProps = new AuthenticationProperties
            {
                RedirectUri = redirectUrl
            };

            var authSchemes = new string[] {
                CookieAuthenticationDefaults.AuthenticationScheme,
                OpenIdConnectDefaults.AuthenticationScheme
            };

            return Results.SignOut(authProps, authSchemes);
        });
```

This navigates to the Azure B2C end session (logout) endpoint. The GET request is successful and I am successully redirected back to the post_logout_redirect_uri in my frontend.

So this all works as expected.

The issue occurs when I pre-emptively log the user out when the HttpContext session expires (if the value for key SessionKeys.EXPIRES_AT doesn't exist I know the session has expired bc the data is deleted). Only the session has expired - the cookies and tokens are still valid. To do this I am using the YARP pipeline middleware per the [documenation](https://microsoft.github.io/reverse-proxy/articles/middleware.html). I've tried three different logout strategies:

```
public static void UseGatewayPipeline(this IReverseProxyApplicationBuilder pipeline)
    {
        var gatewayService = pipeline.ApplicationServices.GetRequiredService<GatewayService>();

        pipeline.Use(async (ctx, next) =>
        {
            var expiry = ctx.Session.GetString(SessionKeys.EXPIRES_AT);
            if (expiry.IsNullOrEmpty())
            {
                 // session has expired so log user out of Azure B2C
                 < signout strategy here (see below) >
            }
            else
            {
                // add access token to request before processing
                await gatewayService.AddToken(ctx);
                await next().ConfigureAwait(false);
            }
        });
```

I've tried the following signout strategies:

SignOutAsync async 
```
var authProps = new AuthenticationProperties
{
       RedirectUri = "/"
 };
await ctx.SignOutAsync(CookieAuthenticationDefaults.AuthenticationScheme);
await ctx.SignOutAsync(OpenIdConnectDefaults.AuthenticationScheme, authProps);
```

Redirect Response
```
var logoutEndpoint = "https://<registry>.b2clogin.com/<registry>.onmicrosoft.com/b2c_1a_signin-controlim-oidc-local-withexpiry-dev/oauth2/v2.0/logout?post_logout_redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Flocalhost%3A8080%2Fsignout-callback-oidc&x-client-SKU=ID_NETSTANDARD2_0&x-client-ver=6.15.1.0&max_age=0";
ctx.Response.Redirect(logout);
```

Results.SignOut
```
var authSchemes = new string[]
{
    CookieAuthenticationDefaults.AuthenticationScheme,
    OpenIdConnectDefaults.AuthenticationScheme
};
await Results.SignOut(authProps, authSchemes).ExecuteAsync(ctx);
```

In each case the result is the exactly same. The GET request to the logout endpoint is successfull, but I am not redirected to the post_logout_redirect_uri. So the UI is effectively stuck in this state and it's impossible to re-initiate the login process. 

<img width="1545" alt="image" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/94627216/212474856-befdace5-b81c-4b01-8747-37189237066f.png">

<img width="995" alt="image" src="https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/94627216/212475962-be4b0d18-7ef6-4e2c-b9c8-7278bf2098a7.png">

Why am I not redirected to the post_logout_redirect_uri? Is it possible to initiate the call to the logout endpoint from the server? I've tried to initiate it a couple other ways from the server and have never gotten it to work. It only works when I initiate it from the frontend.

I could really use some help to figure out how to log the user out such that I am redirected to the post_logout_redirect_uri.

### Expected Behavior

I am redirected to the post_logout_redirect_uri after logout.

